+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018tiapW3A7xnWiGu19ggRiQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The document management API is complete. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Architecture\n\n**8 source files** in `src/`:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `types.ts` | TypeScript interfaces for User, Folder, Document, Permission, ActivityEntry |\n| `store.ts` | In-memory store factory using Maps and arrays |\n| `auth.ts` | Registration, login, token-based auth middleware |\n| `permissions.ts` | Role-based access control with hierarchy traversal |\n| `folders.ts` | Folder CRUD with cascade delete |\n| `documents.ts` | Document CRUD with activity logging |\n| `sharing.ts` | Share resources, update roles, view permissions |\n| `activity.ts` | Activity log endpoint |\n| `app.ts` | `createApp()` factory composing all routes |\n\n## API Routes\n\n- `POST /auth/register` — register user\n- `POST /auth/login` — login, get token\n- `POST/GET/PUT/DELETE /folders/:id` — folder CRUD\n- `POST/GET/PUT/DELETE /documents/:id` — document CRUD\n- `POST /:resourceType/:id/share` — share folder or document\n- `GET /:resourceType/:id/permissions` — view permissions\n- `GET /activity` — activity log (reverse chronological)\n\n## Key Design Decisions (informed by inversion thinking)\n\n1. **Permission inheritance**: `getEffectiveRole()` recursively traverses folder hierarchy and picks the **most permissive** role from all paths\n2. **Cascade delete**: Deleting a folder removes all child folders, documents, and their permissions\n3. **Role hierarchy**: viewer < editor < owner. Editor can share (but not assign owner), owner has full control\n4. **Activity logging**: Tracks document creation, updates, deletion, and sharing events with timestamps and user attribution\n5. **47 tests** covering auth, CRUD, permissions, inheritance, edge cases, and the activity log"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usa